Fourteen people sustained injuries when a taxi crashed into a tree off the R529 Giyani Road near Letsitele in Limpopo.It is believed that the driver lost control of the taxi, causing it to veer off the road and crash into the tree. Local authorities will launch an investigation into the exact cause of the collision.Paramedics found a man lying trapped inside the front seat of the taxi.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said &#8220;provincial fire services utilize specialized rescue equipment to free the man from the taxi&#8221;.&#8220;Once the man had been freed, paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and was in a serious condition,&#8221;Meiring said.The rest of passengers sustained minor injuries and were treated at the the Letaba Provincial Hospital.-TNA Reporter 